teams.strDescriptionEN:
The full Canoe Sprint Team who will compete at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games has been announced.
Deborah Kerr and Emily Lewis will race in the K1 Women’s 500m and 200m respectively and will have the opportunity to double up on the Sea Forest Waterway.
They join reigning champion Liam Heath MBE who earned his spot on the team after winning gold at the 2019 World Championship. The fourth team member is Scotlands Katie Reid.

teams.strTeam: Sao Tome and Principe Canoe Sprint
